  "prompt": "How does WhatsApp work? What is the protocol used for communication?",
  "response": "WhatsApp uses several key technologies and protocols for communication:\n\n1. Communication Protocol:\n- WhatsApp primarily uses the XMPP (Extensible Messaging and Presence Protocol) as its base communication protocol\n- Later versions developed a custom proprietary protocol called WhatsApp Web Protocol (WAWP)\n\n2. End-to-End Encryption:\n- Uses Signal Protocol (developed by Open Whisper Systems)\n- Provides end-to-end encryption for messages, voice calls, and video calls\n- Uses public/private key cryptography\n- Each message has a unique encryption key\n\n3. Network Architecture:\n- Client-server model\n- Uses WebSocket for real-time communication\n- Messages routed through WhatsApp's servers\n- Servers handle message routing, delivery, and synchronization\n\n4. Technical Details:\n- Uses TLS/SSL for secure connection\n- Supports UDP and TCP protocols\n- Utilizes STUN/TURN servers for NAT traversal during voice/video calls\n- Uses push notifications for message delivery\n\n5. Connection Methods:\n- Mobile app\n- Web client (WhatsApp Web)\n- Desktop application\n\nThe combination of these technologies enables secure, fast, and reliable messaging across different platforms.",
